   Richard D. Fantozzi, M.D.


Photo of Richard D. Fantozzi, M.D.

                                  Dr. Richard D. Fantozzi was appointed to the Division of Licensing by
   Governor Gray Davis in 2001. An otolaryngologist, he is a member of the
   American Academy of Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery and is a
   fellow of the American Academy of Otolaryngology and Head and Neck
   Surgery, and the American College of Surgeons. He is an active fellow
   in the American Triologic Society. He served on the Scripps Clinic
   Respiratory Care Committee, Managed Care Utilization Review Committee,
   and serves on the Clinic's Head and Neck Tumor Board. He was a
   co-director for Scripps Clinic Division of Head and Neck Surgery and
   Otology.

   Dr. Fantozzi earned his medical doctorate degree from the University of
   Illinois College of Medicine. He completed his postgraduate education
   at the University of California, San Francisco.

